    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay thanks. that makes sense. but i'm a bit worried about how broad that list of things is—like \"losses, damages, liabilities, deficiencies, claims, etc.\" it feels a bit like they're trying to cover every single possible thing that could go wrong. is there a way to narrow that down so i'm not on the hook for stuff that's totally out of my control?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, that's a valid concern. The clause you're reading is a generic \"catch-all\" provision, which can be challenging to navigate. To limit your liability, you can consider seeking clarification from the client or negotiating lighter language in your contract. Some possible approaches include limiting the scope of the clause or imposing specific conditions on when the clause would activate. It's essential to carefully review your contract and consider any potential concessions with caution.",
      "source": "target",
